# Key Achievements

- Successfully validated dataset quality.
- Confirmed there were no missing values.
- Detected and handled outliers using the IQR method.
- Improved feature distributions through preprocessing.
- Extracted seasonal crop information for better recommendations.
- Prepared the dataset for machine learning using train-test splitting.

---

# Conclusion

Epic 3 successfully transformed the raw agricultural dataset into a clean, structured, and machine learning-ready dataset. Through preprocessing techniques such as missing value detection, outlier handling, seasonal crop extraction, and train-test splitting, the dataset was optimized for model development. These preprocessing steps improve prediction accuracy, reduce bias, and establish a strong foundation for the machine learning models implemented in the next phase of the OptiCrop project.

